## 🔧 IMPLEMENTAÇÃO TÉCNICA

### Registradores Utilizados

**Lists:**
- RAX: List pointer
- RBX: Index / Length
- RCX: Data pointer / Capacity
- RDX: Offset calculation
- R8: Value
- R15: Temporary list pointer

**Maps:**
- RAX: Map pointer
- RBX: Key
- RCX: Size
- RDX: Buckets pointer
- R8: Value
- R15: Temporary map pointer

**Structs:**
- RAX: Struct pointer
- RBX: Field value
- RCX: Type ID
- R15: Temporary struct pointer

### Instruções x86-64 Adicionadas

```assembly
# Memory operations
mov [reg + offset], value_reg
mov dest, [reg + offset]
shl reg, imm
add reg, imm
sub reg, imm

# List operations
call matter_alloc
mov [r15], type_tag
mov [r15 + 8], length
mov [r15 + 16], capacity
mov [r15 + 24], data_ptr

# Bounds checking (TODO)
cmp index, length
jge panic_bounds
```

### Runtime Functions Necessárias

```rust
// Memory allocation
fn matter_alloc(size: usize) -> *mut u8;

// List operations
fn matter_list_resize(list: *mut List, new_capacity: usize);

// Map operations
fn matter_map_hash(key: i64) -> usize;
fn matter_map_insert(map: *mut Map, key: i64, value: i64);
fn matter_map_lookup(map: *mut Map, key: i64) -> Option<i64>;

// Struct operations
fn matter_struct_field_offset(type_id: i64, field: &str) -> usize;
```

